@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}
<h1 class="text-center text-success">@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<h4>
    Last Updated: 8/21/2023
</h4>
<p class="fs-5">
    Welcome to Watch Store. This Privacy Policy is designed to help you understand how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your personal information. By accessing or using our website and services, you signify your consent to the practices described in this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy, please do not use our website or services
</p>
<h4 class="text-danger">
    Information We Collect
</h4>
<p class="fs-5">
    We may collect certain personal information from you when you visit our website, make a purchase, sign up for our newsletter, or interact with us in other ways. The types of personal information we may collect include:
</p>
<ul class="fs-5">
    <li>
        Contact Information: Your name, email address, phone number, and mailing address.
    </li>
    <li>
        Payment Information: Credit card or other payment information for purchase transactions.
    </li>
    <li>
        Account Information: Usernames, passwords, and other account-related information.
    </li>
    <li>
        Demographic Information: Age, gender, and other demographic details
    </li>
    <li>
        Usage Data: Information about how you interact with our website, such as pages visited and actions taken.
    </li>
</ul>
<h4 class="text-primary">
    How We Use Your Information
</h4>
<p class="fs-5">
    We use the information we collect for various purposes, including:
</p>
<ul class="fs-5">
    <li>
        Providing and Improving Services: To process orders, fulfill requests, and improve user experience.
    </li>
    <li>
        Marketing: To send promotional emails, newsletters, and offers.
    </li>
    <li>
        Personalization: To customize your experience and provide tailored content.
    </li>
    <li>
        Analytics: To analyze website usage and improve our services.
    </li>
    <li>
        Communication: To respond to your inquiries and provide customer support.
    </li>
</ul>
<h4 class="text-success">Your Choices</h4>
<ul class="fs-5">
    <li>
        Email Communication: You can unsubscribe from our marketing emails by following the unsubscribe link provided in each email.
    </li>
    <li>
        Cookies: You can manage your cookie preferences using your browser settings.
    </li>
    <li>
        Account Information: You can update your account information by logging into your account.
    </li>
</ul>